	<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="">Adam Wiggins was interviewed recently by yours truly, and Satish Talim.</span><br /><span style=""><br /></span><br /><span style="">You can read the <a href="http://rubylearning.com/blog/2009/03/13/interview-adam-wiggins-on-heroku/">full interview here</a> .</span><br /><span style=""><br /></span><br /><span style="">Excerpt follows:</span><br /><span style=""><br /></span><br /><blockquote><div style="line-height: 22px; font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 14px;"><div style="margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;"><span style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; color: #cc3333;"><strong style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">Satish Talim&gt;&gt;</strong> Welcome, Adam and thanks for taking out time to share your thoughts. For the benefit of the readers, could you tell us something about your self?</span></div></div>
<div style="margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">
<strong style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">Adam Wiggins&gt;&gt;</strong> By day, I’m a Rubyist and entrepeneur. By night, I evangelize critical thinking and skepticism, pontificate about economics and cognition, and hack on music software and video games. Some people have said that I’m a nice guy, but I vehemently deny such a vicious rumor!</div>
<div style="margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">I blog at: <a href="http://adam.blog.heroku.com/" style="color: #2361a1; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; text-decoration: underline;">http://adam.blog.heroku.com/</a>
</div>
<blockquote class="right" style="border-bottom-color: rgb(170, 170, 170); border-bottom-width: 3px !important; border-color: initial; border-left-color: rgb(170, 170, 170); border-left-width: 0px !important; border-right-color: rgb(170, 170, 170); border-right-width: 0px !important; border-top-color: rgb(170, 170, 170); border-top-width: 3px !important; color: #666666; float: right; font-size: 1.4em; line-height: 1.222em; margin-bottom: 5px; margin-left: 15px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 5px; padding-bottom: 0px !important; padding-left: 0px !important; padding-right: 0px !important; padding-top: 0px !important; text-align: center;"><div style="margin-bottom: 0px !important; margin-left: 0px !important; margin-right: 0px !important; margin-top: 0px !important; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">Heroku - It’s fast, it’s easy, and it just works.</div></blockquote>
<div style="margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;"><span style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; color: #cc3333;"><strong style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">Satish&gt;&gt;</strong> What’s Heroku and how did you get involved with it?</span></div>
<div style="margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">
<strong style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">Adam&gt;&gt;</strong> I co-founded Heroku along with my partners Orion and James in autumn 2007. Our elevator pitch is “instant Ruby deployment.” Heroku is the fastest and simplest way to get a Rails, Merb, or Sinatra app into production.</div>
<div style="margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;"><span style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px; color: #cc3333;"><strong style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px;">Satish&gt;&gt;</strong> For a person new to development using Rack and Rack-based web frameworks (like Sinatra, Merb, Ramaze, and Camping), how can Heroku help?</span></div></blockquote><br />For the rest, click <a href="http://rubylearning.com/blog/2009/03/13/interview-adam-wiggins-on-heroku/">here</a> or the title of this post.<p /><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img class="posterous_download_image" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/2949792777916502048-6983386873802695566?l=vgoff.blogspot.com" height="1" alt="" width="1" /></div>]]></content:encoded>
